cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper deals with deep neural networks for learning geometric transformations between point-based shape representations. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including computer vision (cs.CV), computer graphics (cs.GR), machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL) for text-based shape representations. However, given the focus on geometric transformations, cs.CV and cs.GR are the most likely sub-categories.
